No idea what&#39;s actually happening, but some theories worth a close look:

- might the crawler host(s) have triggered some bad-behavior 
countermeasures (due to traffic or robots.txt violations) on the target 
server?

- looking closely at the WARC-archived request, is it different in any 
way than the curl-simulation? Especially:
   - byte-for-byte identical in request-path?
   - accept headers?
   - cookies?
   - caching headers (esp. if-modified-since or if-none-match)

It looks like the target URI may be performing an on-the-fly rollup of 
multiple resources, so despite the &#39;_static&#39; implication of the path, it 
may have too-clever logic that&#39;s mishandling the crawler request.

- Gordon

